[0m[49m[39m  107,  99[0m:[39m[49m ## Further Reading
[0m[49m[39m  108, 100[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 109     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - [Apache cTAKES](https://ctakes.apache.org/) - the open-source clinical NLP pipeline from Mayo Clinic that implements many of the techniques discussed in this chapter
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 110     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - [NegEx Algorithm](https://doi.org/10.1016/S1532-0464(01)00029-6) - Chapman et al.'s foundational 2001 paper on negation detection in clinical text
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 111     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - [SciSpaCy](https://allenai.github.io/scispacy/) - spaCy models trained on biomedical text, useful for clinical NER and entity linking
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 112     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - [UMLS (Unified Medical Language System)](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/index.html) - the NLM's comprehensive biomedical terminology resource that underpins most clinical concept normalization
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 113     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - [i2b2/n2c2 NLP Research Datasets](https://portal.dbmi.hms.harvard.edu/projects/n2c2-nlp/) - shared tasks and annotated clinical corpora that have driven clinical NLP research for two decades
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [Clinical Natural Language Processing for Radiology: Exploiting the Text](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26133894/) - foundational survey of clinical NLP techniques and their applications
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [spaCy](https://spacy.io/) - the production NLP framework used throughout this chapter
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [scispaCy](https://allenai.github.io/scispacy/) - biomedical NLP models built on spaCy
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [medspaCy](https://github.com/medspacy/medspacy) - clinical text processing toolkit extending spaCy with assertion detection, context analysis, and section tagging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [UMLS (Unified Medical Language System)](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/index.html) - the NLM meta-thesaurus referenced throughout this chapter
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [i2b2/n2c2 NLP Research Data Sets](https://www.i2b2.org/NLP/DataSets/) - clinical NLP challenge datasets for training and benchmarking
